Split on `\s+MRS\s+` and then prepend `MRS` to the second part of the split:

&lt;!-- language: java --&gt;

    String input = &quot;Alison Quek Yong Hoon MRS Alison Teng Yong Hoon&quot;;
    String[] parts = input.split(&quot;\\s+MRS\\s+&quot;);
    parts[1] = &quot;MRS &quot; + parts[1];
    System.out.println(Arrays.toString(parts));

    // [Alison Quek Yong Hoon, MRS Alison Teng Yong Hoon]

If you really want to use a lookaround, then you should be using a positive _lookahead_:

&lt;!-- language: java --&gt;

    String input = &quot;Alison Quek Yong Hoon MRS Alison Teng Yong Hoon&quot;;
    String[] parts = input.split(&quot;\\s+(?=MRS\\b)&quot;);
    System.out.println(Arrays.toString(parts));

    // [Alison Quek Yong Hoon, MRS Alison Teng Yong Hoon]

